 -- Window Maker Live <wmlive@users.sf.net>  Fri, 10 May 2013 19:22:46 +0200

ultrabay-scripts (0.9-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Added a short note to the control file and README.Debian regarding
    Thinkpads with an Ivy Bridge processor (X230, T430, T530, etc.) not
    being supported by tp-smapi, resulting in no battery threshold
    management being available via the ultrabay_battery script,

  * Added some preliminary, but not yet functional support for battery
    management via acpi_call and tpacpi-bat to both ultrabay_battery and
    ultrabay_common. Some user of a current Thinkpad with an Ivy Bridge
    CPU please help wth this.

  * Upon popular request, changed the '#!/bin/bash' shebang to POSIX
    conformant '#!/bin/sh'.

 -- Window Maker Live <wmlive@users.sf.net>  Wed, 08 May 2013 22:00:56 +0200

ultrabay-scripts (0.8-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Revised test expression in functions "ultrabay_dock_interface ()"
    and "ultrabay_battery_interface ()" in ultrabay_common. Thanks to
    user dywi from www.thinkpad-forum.de for making me aware.

  * Moved the check for SMAPI from the ultrabay_battery script into a
    generic function "thinkpad_smapi_check ()" in ultrabay_common, and
    use this function instead in the script.

  * Included icons battery.png and cogwheels.png and modified icon path
    accordingly to a more generic /usr/share/icons/ in ultrabay_common,
    thus avoiding to rely on a user's ~/GNUstep/Library/Icons directory.

